like my grandpa used to say to me before a race : luck is for losers , do your homework and you won't need good luck . all i would wish to you is success and not to have bad luck
cover up done @memorialbrooklyn

another @vermontoverland on the books ! hands down the most brutal race of the season , and this year’s course didn’t lower the bar for sure with more class-4 segments and some of them even more technical than before .
tire game was very important , the @ircbike_official  boken doublecross proved again to be the best tire on every condition .
 eating was extremely hard with such technical descents so i opted for the super-high carb mix from @skratchlabs skratchlabs in one bottle , the high-sodium in the other bottle and some bars in my pockets.
as always , the @velocioapparel luxe V2 is my go to for every race and the concept radiator jersey to keep everything in place and moving less on my back pockets .
thanks again @anseldickey for an amazing event and a touching speech before the start .
i’ll see you next year for sure !

Jersey Gravel Deux 
My Race: this was a timed segment race (which im not a fan , and my first time doing that kind of race) and it was cut short from 100 to 86 miles .
race started easy and with the heavy rain coming in the afternoon i decided to just keep a sustained pace and finish as early as possible to avoid getting drenched , some people joined but most of them got dropped early leaving only me and two more riders “playing rough” till one of them got dropped and the second one got a flat leaving me by myself for the rest of the day. pushed a bit harder on the segments bot not really trying anything crazy so i could keep a fast pace . had to stop for a while to find my go-pro after i dropped it but kept going as soon as i found it .
The Race : course was AMAZING , mostly flat with a couple of very easy rolling hills and no technical trails or roads .
uploading the course after they change it was pretty hard , but got to do it last minute . it was very well marked and police on every major intersection.
only stopped once at one of the aid stations (needed to pee) and they had lots of options , gels , coke , bananas and savory food.
the only downside with the race have been the results , they took for ever to post them , im not even on them , and i saw a bunch of people posting the same problem .kudos for the vegan food options !

The Gear : opted for the 42 mm @ircbike_official boken doublecross ( im doing a boken doublecross in the front boken in the back next time) 
@trekbikes checkpoint SLR with @shimanogravel  GRX/ultegra mullet 
and @velocioapparel 
luxe V2 bibs
ziperless signature jersey with a SE long sleeve on top ( it was rainy and around 60°) 
luxe gloves (always my choice for gravel races because of the cushion) .
Nutrition : @skratchlabs super high carb in one bottle and high sodium in the other bottle , a few pistachio bars from and the energy chews , all from @skratchlabs got me@to the finish like 
last but not least , thanks to @vince_rides_the_world and @tuned.by for having my bike ready for the race !
i recommend this race as an entry to gravel racing , i’ll be back next year for sure @readysetgoadventures
tons of new flash on my wall , come say hi and pick something , check our collection of tattoo history books or lets make something happen with your ideas !
from a couple of months ago

•the quick and the dead•
@mt.davisgravelgrinder 
My race: after a week with only one ride i was freaking out about this race , it was on saturday after the flooding and i had to leave in the middle of it with my friend @francoisdavid1981 and we made it to PA kinda late where our friend @bretton_beard let us stay for the night . started pretty hard after the neutral start and hung with the front group for a few miles till i decided to step back a bit before blowing , and i was by myself yoyoing with other riders for the rest of the day  felt surprisingly fresh all day and finished 12th over all , 6th in my category .
The Race: this is a proper race ,a 76 mile course without trails sounds good , man this was a VERY tough course , perfect roads all day , nothing technical no single track but one steep climb after the other ALL ADAY ! the general organization of the race was on point, very well marked, lots of volunteers on every intersection, i did t stop , but aid stations looked very good and the had the option of sending your gear and they had it there for you.
 awesome vibes but again, this is a proper race 
the gear: i didnt change anything on my bike
@ircbike_official  boken doublecross front and rear at 30 and 33 psi 
@trekbikes checkpoint SLR with @shimanogravel  GRX/ultegra combo
it was warmer and no rain so i used the @velocioapparel concept radiator jersey this is a very breathable jersey adjusts perfect to the body and it has and reinforced back pockets so your stuff dont move .
as always, LUXE V2 bib shorts and luxe gloves .
Nutrition : i did two bottles of @skratchlabs super high carb , and one high sofium i put in a bottle someone hand me at the aid station , two bags of @skratchlabs chews with caffeine and a couple of gels at the end .
100% recommend this race to push yourself of simply as a challenge ! . i will be there next year for sure !

@crossmountaincrusher MY RACE : ok, call it a ride, a race , whatever you wanna call it, it was HARD. neutral was very easy, but after a spin around the town the police car pulled out and the pace increased right away leaving a group of around 20 riders that exploded on the first steep climb where i stayed with a group of 4.
had to stop at the top of the climb to turn my rear derailleur on cause i knew the descent was pretty chunky  caught up with them on the descent ended up with only two other riders, one got dropped on the next descent and the other one dropped me on the last climb, got caught by someone else with 15 miles to go but dropped him on the last mile . ended up second . legs felt good all day.
drove the night before and stayed in a beautiful tiny home with @gracefilley and that made an amazing weekend 
 THE “RACE” : this was my second time doing this event , the course is great , beautiful views and they added a fun climb at the end. mixed terrain between very well maintained gravel roads and pavement.is not supposed to be a race but hey, there’s a good price for the first person to finish and its GOOD ! the vibes are good with super strong riders.
they had great food with vegan options the registration ,🙏🏻 thanks for that ! i saw a few aid stations along the way but i did t stop
in my opinion , it lacks coverage and exposure, and those important factors when you’re asking sponsors to support you to attend. this is a good event for any gravel cyclist , there was groups at any pace you want to ride , and good vibes.
THE GEAR: opted for the @ircbike_official BOKEN front and rear at 29 and 32 PSI rolling resistance was great and this tire makes me feel super safe on fast corners because of the threaded sides. everything @trekbikes CHECKPOINT SLR worked perfect ! 
it was supposed to be cold so i used the  @velocioapparel thermal long sleeve with the gravel base layer , i love the pockets . the long gravel glove did a prefect job for the 40-50° weather and of course the LUXE V2 bib shorts .
NUTRITION: it was only 62 miles so, so two bottles of @skratchlabs super high carb a bar and two caffein chews were enough fuel
